headline: AI ‘Roadkill’ Fears Haunt Traders Two Years After ChatGPT Debut
summary: (Bloomberg) -- The rise of ChatGPT sparked fears about artificial intelligence roiling businesses of all kinds. Two years after the chatbot’s release, the results haven’t been nearly as cataclysmic as some investors predicted. headline: Here's How Many Shares of Accenture You Should Own to Get $1,000 in Yearly Dividends
summary: One of the more closely watched stocks in the tech world lately has been consulting company Accenture (NYSE: ACN).  Unlike the typical tech (or tech-adjacent) stock, Accenture is a steady, and reliable, dividend payer, handing out a shareholder distribution every quarter.  In October, Accenture and top AI equipment and solutions supplier Nvidia announced a significant expansion of their existing partnership.
